performance_optimizations.description:
Q6 has a tight filter loop that's memory-bandwidth bound. Two micro-optimizations:

1. Hoist constants and simplify branch structure:
   - Current: 5 separate if conditions in the loop
   - Optimized: Combine conditions with && to enable short-circuit evaluation and better branch prediction
   - Store filter constants outside loop to avoid repeated loads

2. Manual loop unrolling (process 4 rows per iteration):
   - Reduces loop overhead and enables better instruction-level parallelism
   - Compiler may already do this with -O2, but can make it explicit

In queries/q6.cpp:
```cpp
size_t n = lineitem.size();
const int32_t* shipdate = lineitem.l_shipdate.data();
const double* price = lineitem.l_extendedprice.data();
const double* discount = lineitem.l_discount.data();
const double* quantity = lineitem.l_quantity.data();

double revenue = 0.0;
for (size_t i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    int32_t date = shipdate[i];
    double disc = discount[i];
    double qty = quantity[i];

    // Combined condition for better branch prediction
    if (date >= min_date && date < max_date &&
        disc >= min_discount && disc <= max_discount &&
        qty < max_quantity) {
        revenue += price[i] * disc;
    }
}
```

Expected improvement: Minor (5-10%) - Q6 will still be bottlenecked by memory bandwidth until zone maps are implemented.

Q1 computes multiple expressions using l_extendedprice, l_discount, l_tax. Optimize the inner loop for better cache locality.

In queries/q1.cpp:
- Cache vector data pointers outside the loop to avoid repeated std::vector method calls
- Precompute discount factor: double disc_factor = 1.0 - discount;
- Fuse multiplications: double disc_price = price * disc_factor; double charge = disc_price * (1.0 + tax);
- Process in blocks to keep data in cache

```cpp
const int32_t* shipdate = lineitem.l_shipdate.data();
const double* qty_data = lineitem.l_quantity.data();
const double* price_data = lineitem.l_extendedprice.data();
const double* disc_data = lineitem.l_discount.data();
const double* tax_data = lineitem.l_tax.data();
const uint8_t* returnflag_data = lineitem.l_returnflag_code.data();
const uint8_t* linestatus_data = lineitem.l_linestatus_code.data();

for (size_t i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    if (shipdate[i] > max_date) continue;

    size_t idx = returnflag_data[i] * 2 + linestatus_data[i];
    double qty = qty_data[i];
    double price = price_data[i];
    double disc = disc_data[i];
    double tax = tax_data[i];

    double disc_factor = 1.0 - disc;
    double disc_price = price * disc_factor;

    agg_array[idx].sum_qty += qty;
    agg_array[idx].sum_base_price += price;
    agg_array[idx].sum_disc_price += disc_price;
    agg_array[idx].sum_charge += disc_price * (1.0 + tax);
    agg_array[idx].sum_discount += disc;
    agg_array[idx].count++;
}
```

Expected improvement: Modest - eliminates virtual function call overhead from std::vector::operator[], better register allocation.
